cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about visual object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a new approach for optimizing the two modules of a CNN-based object detector, which involves selecting anchors and jointly optimizing classification and localization. This approach involves multiple instance learning and iterative selection processes, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on the MS-COCO object detection benchmark, which involves evaluating the performance of object detection algorithms. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category.
